src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif></span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#E09C5F>(8/31/01 11:41:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pale riders gather in the Shadow of Luclin</span><hr size=1> My sarcastic comments were directed to the fact that horses are something that should've been in the game since day 1.  Many players have been requesting them and now it seems when they are finally implemented their usefulness will be limited to the new expansion zones.    Indeed, the timing of this annoucement seems geared towards keeping people from running off to DAoC, Shadowbane, or any of the other next generation MMORPGs coming out soon.  &quot;Just wait for our new Luclin expansion! The gnomes will look like dirty, old men and we'll have HORSES for all the kids!&quot;.<br>
<br>
I'm also curious how they will work.  From the description it sounds like players will have a whistle to call their horse from their stable whenever they want(i.e. right click summon effect).  As far as the running speed of the horse, will it be the same or faster than SoW? Will it be able to contribute to combat - i.e. give/take damage? Also, will you be able to name your horse or will you be stuck with one of those random lame summoned pet names?<br>
<br>
For everyone's sake I hope they don't allow players to bring them into the cities or dungeons.  Its bad enough trying to squeeze past some buttscratching ogre to get into the bank.<br>
<br>
